name: Able Body Labor
overview:
Able Body Labor Company operates as a temporary staffing company. The company offers disaster recovery staffing services in the areas of debris clean-up, building repair, laying sandbags, move equipment and plants, and installing hurricane shutters and plywood. It also offers event staffing workers, including ticket takers, parking attendants, setup and cleanup crews, concessionaires, parking auditors, ushers, bathroom attendants, and security; and hotel and restaurant staff, such as banquet servers, dishwashers, housekeepers, chefs/cooks, janitors, hosts/hostesses, cashiers, and front desk staff. In addition, the company provides industrial workers, including warehouse personnel, assemblers, inventory and shipping clerks, conveyor tenders, material handlers, bottlers, package seal and fork lift operators, stockers, and sorters. Further, it provides construction workers, such as clean-up crews, movers, diggers, laborers, landscapers, flaggers, hangers, finishers, plumbers, painters, finish/trim carpenters, CDL drivers, welders, metal framers, HVAC professionals, rod busters, jobsite foremen, roofers, and masons.

The company has locations in New York, Delaware, California, Nevada, Utah, Arizona, Colorado, Texas, Louisiana, Mississippi, Alabama, Georgia, Florida, South Carolina, North Carolina, and Virginia. Able Body Labor Company was founded in 1986 and is based in Clearwater, Florida.
